{
  "info": {
    "name": "Ecert Document Review API",
    "description": "Tour guiado (ES): las carpetas est\u00e1n ordenadas como recorrido \u2014 Health \u2192 Register \u2192 Consult \u2192 Status transitions \u2192 Observations \u2192 History \u2192 Versions \u2192 Validation. Ejec\u00fatelas en ese orden (o use el Collection Runner). Para los requests que suben archivo, seleccione los PDF incluidos en la carpeta `samples/` del repositorio (contrato-v1.pdf y contrato-v2.pdf).\n\nManual test collection for the ecert Document Review API.\n\nHow to use:\n1. Start the stack: `docker compose up --build` (API on http://localhost:8080).\n2. Open the 'Register document (201)' request, go to Body > form-data, and for the `File` row click 'Select Files' and pick `samples/contrato-v1.pdf` from this repository (any real .pdf works). The other requests reuse the returned id automatically via the `documentId` collection variable.\n\nThe `baseUrl` variable defaults to http://localhost:8080 \u2014 change it under the collection's Variables tab if needed.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8080",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "documentId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "createdDocumentId",
      "value": ""
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health check",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "health"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Liveness/readiness probe. Returns 'Healthy' when the API and its Postgres connection are up."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Register",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register document (201)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201 Created', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(201); });",
                  "pm.test('has Location header', function () { pm.response.to.have.header('Location'); });",
                  "var json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('status is Created and version 1', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('Created');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.currentVersionNumber).to.eql(1);",
                  "});",
                  "if (json && json.id) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('documentId', json.id);",
                  "  console.log('Saved documentId =', json.id);",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "Title",
                  "value": "My Contract",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "Type",
                  "value": "Contract",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "UploadedBy",
                  "value": "tiago",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "File",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": "samples/contrato-v1.pdf"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Registers a new document plus its first PDF version (multipart/form-data).\n\nBEFORE SENDING: in Body > form-data, set the `File` row's type to 'File' (dropdown on the key) and select a real .pdf.\n\nValid `Type` values: Contract, Annex, Quotation, Report, Other.\n\nDo NOT add a Content-Type header manually \u2014 Postman sets the multipart boundary for you.\n\nOn success returns 201 + Location header; the test script saves the new id into the `documentId` variable for the Consult requests. The uploaded PDF is analyzed with PdfPig on the server; a parseable file gets its real page count stored on the version (pageCount in responses), an unparseable one is stored with pageCount null.\n\nFile to select: `samples/contrato-v1.pdf` (from this repository)."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Consult",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get document by id (200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('returns the requested id', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().id).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('documentId'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Full detail for one document, including its version history. Uses the `documentId` captured by the Register request."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List all documents (200)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Lists document summaries (no version array). Includes the 3 seeded documents plus anything you register."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List by status (200)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents?status=Created",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "status",
                  "value": "Created",
                  "description": "One of: Created, PendingReview, UnderReview, Approved, Rejected, Archived"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Filter by status. Try Approved / Rejected / PendingReview to see the seeded documents in other states."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "List by type (200)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents?type=Report",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents"
              ],
              "query": [
                {
                  "key": "type",
                  "value": "Report",
                  "description": "One of: Contract, Annex, Quotation, Report, Other"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Filter by document type. `status` and `type` can be combined."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Status transitions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Submit for review (200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('document is PendingReview', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('PendingReview');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"PendingReview\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"tiago\",\n  \"details\": \"Submitted for review\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Moves the registered document from Created to PendingReview. Valid target statuses depend on the current status (state machine): Created -> PendingReview -> UnderReview -> Approved | Rejected; Approved -> Archived; Rejected -> PendingReview | Archived.\n\nRun the Status transitions requests in order after Register: they walk the document Created -> PendingReview -> UnderReview -> Rejected."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Start review (200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('document is UnderReview', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('UnderReview');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"UnderReview\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"maria.reviewer\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "PendingReview -> UnderReview. `details` is optional; when omitted the audit event gets a default note."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject without reason (400)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 400', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(400); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"Rejected\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"maria.reviewer\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Rejecting requires a `reason` -> 400 'A reason is required when rejecting a document.' The document must be UnderReview (an illegal reject would be 409 instead)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reject with reason (200)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('document is Rejected', function () {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.eql('Rejected');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"Rejected\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"maria.reviewer\",\n  \"reason\": \"Totals on page 2 do not match the annex.\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "UnderReview -> Rejected. The `reason` is stored as a RejectionReason observation on the current version, alongside ObservationAdded and StatusChanged audit events. Check with 'Get document by id'."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Invalid transition (409)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 409', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(409); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"Approved\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"maria.reviewer\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/{{documentId}}/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "{{documentId}}",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "A Rejected document cannot be Approved directly -> 409 ProblemDetails 'Cannot move from Rejected to Approved.' (Rejected can only go to PendingReview or Archived.)"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Change status unknown id (404)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 404', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(404); });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"targetStatus\": \"PendingReview\",\n  \"performedBy\": \"tiago\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/documents/11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111/status",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "documents",
                "11111111-1111-1111-1111-111111111111",
                "status"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Unknown id returns a 404 ProblemDetails body."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Observations",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Add comment (201)",
